{
  "id": 133039,
  "referenceId": 109093,
  "name": "Revelation 13:1–18",
  "localizedName": "Revelation 13:1–18",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In the vision, John saw a beast come out of the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108072",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "sea"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". He saw another beast come out of the earth. They were like the four animals Daniel saw in a vision recorded in Daniel chapter 7."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In Daniel’s vision, beasts were signs of human governments. Thrones were signs of authority and horns were signs of power. This was true for John’s vision as well. The first beast was a sign of a powerful ruler or government. The second beast was a sign of a person or group that supported them."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In Revelation 16:13 the second beast was also called a false prophet. The devil was the dragon who gave these beasts power over people. The first beast was allowed to rule for "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108187",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "42 months"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". The second beast made people worship the first beast and be marked in a certain way."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "This was the opposite of when God’s servants were marked by God’s seal. The mark of the beast from the sea was the number "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108188",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "666"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". All of this was like something happening in John’s time in the lands controlled by Rome."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Authorities and rulers made people obey and worship "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108047",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Rome"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and the emperor. Those who refused to worship the Roman ruler "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108034",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Caesar"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " were treated badly or killed."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
